###############################################################################

  This document describes the usage of report, the Trilinos results reporting
  utility.
  
  The report utility provides a standard way to commit Trilinos results to the
  TrilinosTestResults repository and, ultimately the Trilinos test results
  database on software.sandia.gov.
  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
I.  Prerequisites

  In order for the configure utility to work, you must have the following in
  place:
  
    1.  An existing, complete set of results generated by the Trilinos test
        utilities (with original naming scheme intact).
    2.  A local TrilinosTestResults sandbox.  This does not need to contain
        all existing results--in fact it would be overwhelming if it did.  To
        checkout just the top-level directory, use "cvs checkout -l
        TrilinosTestResults"
    3.  An account on software.sandia.gov that can be accessed via ssh and cvs.
       
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
II.  Execution

  To execute the Trilinos build utility, simply type:
  
    cd /PATH/TO/Trilinos/commonTools/test/utilities/
    perl report --help
            
  Refer to this help output for the most up-to-date information on usage and
  available options.  (You can use "./" instead of "perl " if your system's
  perl interpreter resides at /usr/bin/perl)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------